               <p>I live at <placeName id="t17911207-13-crimeloc68">Enfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17911207-13-crimeloc68" type="placeName" value="Enfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17911207-13-crimeloc68" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17911207-13-off66 t17911207-13-crimeloc68"></join> parish; I lost two linen shirts off the line, on the 24th of November; they were found on the prisoner; I did not see them taken from him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17911207-13-person192">
                  BENJAMIN
                   HARVEY
               <interp inst="t17911207-13-person192" type="surname" value="HARVEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17911207-13-person192" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17911207-13-person192" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I was coming from Enfield-highway, and I heard a woman cry Stop thief! that man has got my shirts; and I stopped the prisoner; and my mate, 
               <persName id="t17911207-13-person193">
                  John
                   Smith
               <interp inst="t17911207-13-person193" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17911207-13-person193" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17911207-13-person193" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , came up as the prisoner gave me the shirts; I asked him for them.</p>
               <p>(The shirts produced.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17911207-13-person194">
                  GEORGE
                   LAW
               <interp inst="t17911207-13-person194" type="surname" value="LAW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17911207-13-person194" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17911207-13-person194" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am constable; I produce the shirts; Harvey delivered them to me; he brought the prisoner with him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17911207-13-person195">
                  MARY
                   GERMAIN
               <interp inst="t17911207-13-person195" type="surname" value="GERMAIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17911207-13-person195" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17911207-13-person195" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I know these shirts to be my husband's; they were taken off the line wet; I did not know the prisoner before my little girl told me that a man was taking them; and I ran<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="179112070014"></xptr>after him, and saw Harvey and Smith coming, and they stopped him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17911207-13-person196">
                  JOHN
                   SMITH
               <interp inst="t17911207-13-person196" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17911207-13-person196" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17911207-13-person196" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I was with Harvey when the prosecutor's wife was running after the prisoner, and we pursued him and took him; he said, What do you want? I conducted him to the constable; it was not more than two minutes after the shirts were taken off the line.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was coming from Hertford, and I was coming along; a man overtook me, and travelled about four miles with me; he wanted to borrow sixpence, and I lent him it; he said he lived at a house on the road; he went into a house; he said his sister lived there; and I walked on; and he came out, and gave the bundle to me; and this woman called Halloobulloo, we have a thief now, and I will get enough to keep me all the winter; they took my property from me; I am a stranger in this country, I came from Ireland.</p>
               <p>Court to Mrs. Germain. Had he any bundle? - Nothing but the shirts.</p>
               <p>Jury. Was any other man with him at the time? - No person; he had the shirts on his arm.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17911207-13-verdict69" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17911207-13-verdict69" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. (Aged 60.)</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17911207-13-punish70" type="punishmentDescription">
